From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 01:15:11 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rockchip: rk3576-generic: build the maskrom USB boot images

Enable CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_MASKROM_IMAGE so binman also emits
u-boot-rockchip-usb471.bin and u-boot-rockchip-usb472.bin: the CODE471
(external TPL) and CODE472 (SPL + padding + FIT) payloads the BootROM's
USB download protocol takes in maskrom mode. Pushing those two files
over USB runs the full TPL/SPL/ATF/U-Boot chain from RAM without
touching any storage, which gives a board a bootloader-independent way
to reach a trustworthy rockusb gadget, test-boot an OS from USB, or
recover from a broken boot chain -- mainline's f_rockusb reports short
reads honestly instead of acknowledging data it never transferred.

The normal storage boot is unaffected: the SPL_RAM_DEVICE this selects
is only consulted when board_boot_order() sees the BootROM bootsource
ID say the SPL itself arrived over USB.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
index 15022300..501b1951 100644
--- a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
+++ b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@ CONFIG_COUNTER_FREQUENCY=24000000
 CONFIG_ARCH_ROCKCHIP=y
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="rk3576-generic"
 CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_RK3576=y
+CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_MASKROM_IMAGE=y
 CONFIG_SYS_LOAD_ADDR=0x40c00800
 CONFIG_DEBUG_UART_BASE=0x2AD40000
 CONFIG_DEBUG_UART_CLOCK=24000000
